&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;37.5 Hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward 14 is a 26 bedded Acute Oncology ward. We are currently seeking motivated individuals to join the ward nursing team, applicants for all posts must be able to demonstrate genuine desire to work within this speciality and be committed to delivering high quality patient centred care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our patients are central to everything we do; our nurses provide high standards of care with commitment, compassion and competence. Our teams are innovative and forward thinking with an honest and transparent culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for staff who have a minimum of 2 years experience in Haematology or Oncology, Teaching qualification and be Chemotherapy competent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want the opportunity to make a difference, are committed to delivering high quality care and want to work within a dedicated multi-disciplinary team, we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
